  "data": {
    "description": {
      "chat": "",
      "gmnotes": "",
      "short": "",
      "value": "<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.hIhgdXnqGHBm0A64]{Envoy Improvisation}</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 53\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div title=\"Page 53\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>Through a mix of complex manipulation and other cues, you focus enemies&rsquo; fire on an ally. As a standard action, you can spend 1 Resolve Point and select a willing ally within 30 feet. Until the end of your next turn, enemies within 100 feet of that ally who can sense both you and that ally take a &ndash;4 penalty to all ranged attacks they make that don&rsquo;t target that ally. This ability otherwise acts as if that ally used the @Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.cDTGl7g2ZvJfrccz]{Draw Fire (Ex) (Envoy)} improvisation. You must have the @Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.cDTGl7g2ZvJfrccz]{Draw Fire (Ex) (Envoy)} improvisation to choose this improvisation.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: 'Exo 2', sans-serif; font-size: 13px; background-color: #f2f2f2;\">&nbsp;</span><sub style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-family: 'Exo 2', sans-serif; background-color: #f2f2f2;\"><img style=\"user-select: text;\" src=\"systems/sfrpg/images/cup/gameplay/sense.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" /></sub></p>\n<p><sub>From AP #35 pg. 51</sub></p>",
